      <p><span class="colophon-word">Nomos</span> (νόμος): in Greek thought, law or convention as against nature; in Carl Schmitt's usage, the founding division of the earth from which legal and political order follows. This journal borrows the word to mark its subject: not just events, but the settlements beneath them.</p>
